Package parser.nodes.conditions

This package contains classes that are used to evaluate conditions such as less than, greater than and equal to. It also has a class (NotNode) that is used to process false conditions. If, Else if and Else classes are also contained within this package.
  • Class Summary
    Class Description
    ComparatorNode
    The comparator node is used by priority queues to decide the order in which each object should be dispensed.
    ConditionNode
    This class is used to check whether or not s specific condition is true.
    ElseIfNode
    This class contains deals with executing code in the else if branch of an if statement.
    ElseNode
    This class is attached to if nodes and contains the statements that will be run if the else branch is triggered.
    EqualToNode
    This class is used to check if one var is less than another.
    GreaterThanNode
    This class is used to check if one var is less than another.
    IfNode
    This class is used to run if statements.
    LessThanNode
    This class is used to check if one var is less than another.
    NotNode
    This class checks that a condition is not true.
